1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,400
The James Webb Space Telescope sees a universe Hubble never could.

2
00:00:04,400 --> 00:00:10,000
While Hubble captures stunning optical images, JWST dives into infrared, revealing hidden cosmic secrets.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:16,000
Infrared light penetrates cosmic dust, unveiling stars and galaxies forming over 13 billion years ago.

4
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:22,000
NASA reports JWST's ability to peer further back in time surpasses anything Hubble could achieve.

5
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:27,600
This means we can witness the birth of galaxies, not just their present form.

6
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:32,800
Dive deeper into the mysteries of the universe—follow for more amazing space discoveries!
